  "slug": "pain-de-campagne",
  "title": "Pain de campagne",
  "subtitle": "French sourdough country loaf with an open crumb and crackling crust",
  "excerpt": "A round sourdough loaf made from mostly strong white flour with a small wholemeal addition for colour and flavour. An autolyse rest before adding the levain and salt builds extensible gluten without mechanical work. The dough is folded during a four-hour bulk ferment, shaped into a boule, and retarded in the fridge overnight. Bake in a covered pot for the first 20 minutes to trap steam, then uncover for full crust development.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Pain de campagne (country bread) is a broad category of French sourdough loaves distinguished from baguette by a rounder shape and a proportion of wholemeal or rye flour. The modern high-hydration, autolyse-method version is closely associated with the methods Raymond Calvel documented in Le Goût du Pain (1990), which popularised the autolyse rest in professional and home baking internationally. Calvel's book is in commercial print; the method is otherwise widely disseminated in baking literature and is considered standard practice.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pain de campagne is a French sourdough country loaf: mostly strong white flour with a little wholemeal for colour and flavour. The dough uses an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "autolyse",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "Autolyse",
                  "termId": "cmp87mgal0001dcv47448winm"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " rest before the levain and salt go in, which builds an extensible, smooth dough without heavy kneading. The bake is in a covered pot: the lid traps steam for the first 20 minutes, giving the crust a thin, crackling finish. Allow two days from start to slice."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ingredients"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "strong-bread-flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 450
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "wholemeal-bread-flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 50
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "water",
              "unit": "ml",
              "amount": 340,
              "prepNote": "room temperature"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "sourdough-starter",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 100,
              "prepNote": "active, at peak (fed 4 to 8 hours before)"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "salt-table",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 10
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Autolyse and mix, 40 minutes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Combine both flours with 330 ml of the water in a large bowl. Mix until no dry flour remains. Cover and rest for 40 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the active sourdough starter and the remaining 10 ml of water. Squeeze and fold to incorporate."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the salt. Wet your hand slightly and work it into the dough by pinching and folding for 1 to 2 minutes. The dough should feel slightly sticky but hold its shape."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bulk ferment, 4 hours"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Leave the dough at room temperature (21 to 24°C) for 4 hours."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "During the first 2 hours, do a set of stretch-and-folds every 30 minutes (four sets total). For each set: wet your hand, grab the dough from one side, stretch it upward, and fold it over the top. Rotate the bowl 90 degrees and repeat three more times."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "After the last set, cover and leave undisturbed for the remaining 2 hours. The dough should increase by about 50 percent and feel airy when gently pressed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shape and cold retard overnight"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dust a banneton generously with rice flour."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and pre-shape: fold the edges to the centre to build tension, then flip, cup the dough, and drag it toward you to tighten. Rest uncovered for 20 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Final shape: flip the dough, fold the sides and top to the centre, roll toward you tightly, then place seam-side up in the banneton."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dust the surface, cover, and refrigerate for 10 to 14 hours."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 240°C conventional (220°C fan) with a cast-iron casserole inside for at least 45 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Take the dough straight from the fridge and tip onto a sheet of baking paper. Score quickly with a sharp blade at a 30-degree angle."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Lower into the hot casserole using the paper, replace the lid, and bake for 20 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove the lid and bake for a further 20 to 25 minutes until the crust is deep amber and the internal temperature reaches 96°C."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cool on a rack for at least 1 hour before cutting."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
